      • isCrossingEncapuslation

        public static final boolean isCrossingEncapuslation(List<org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Property> nestedPath)
        Checks if is crossing encapsulation.
        Parameters:
        nestedPath - the nested path
        Returns:
        true, if is crossing encapsulation true if we are breaking encapsulation (see SysML rules in SysML Standard 1.2, p.44): isEncapsulated: Boolean [0..1] If true, then the block is treated as a black box; a part typed by this black box can only be connected via its ports or directly to its outer boundary. If false, or if a value is not present, then connections can be established to elements of its internal structure via deep-nested connector ends.
